item.title: No one can fix this problem
item.dc:creator: @Luvodicus Luvodicus
item.description:
@Luvodicus wrote:

[quote=“MasterHelper, post:1, topic:177060”]i try to connect to my server but it doesnt connect.
i configured the client and all.
even the no-ip is set up.[/quote]

  1. Disable your firewall completely, or make sure it is accepting connections from your port (default port to use is 49345 i think)

  2. Make sure NO-IP executable is running (download it from no-ip.com)
